Pre-Game Insights: Comoros come into AFCON qualifying following an impressive COSAFA Cup campaign
Les Coelacantes failed to qualify for the 2023 edition of the AFCON but have enjoyed an impressive CAF World Cup qualifying campaign
Comoros secured a notable 1-0 win over African giants Ghana in November last year
Gambia has reached the main draw in each of their last two attempts and was knocked out in the group stage earlier this year but did reach the quarter-final back in the 2021-22 edition
Johnny McKinstry took up the management role in mid-May
Gambia has made significant strides forward in recent years and has a few big names arriving in Casablanca for these qualifiers
Miscellaneous Highlights: Comoros' Red Star Belgrade forward Ben El Fardou scored in each of the Comoros' last two World Cup qualification matches
Momodou Lion Njie and Lamin Saidy will be hoping to make their debuts for Gambia
Derby County midfielder Ebou Adams and Brighton & Hove Albion's new winger Yankuba Minteh have also made the trip to Morocco with the squad
Comoros possible starting lineup: Boina; Omari, Zahary, Soilihi, Boura; Bourhane, Madji, Ahmed, Selemeni, Maolida; Fardou
Gambia possible starting lineup: Jarjue; Colley, J Ceesay, Gomez, Njie; Adams, A Ceesay, Barrow, Fadera, Minteh, Sidibeh
